<h1 id="title">ui-number-input</h1>
<h2>HTML <b>Number</b> input with Bootstrap and mobile friendly features</h2>

<h3>
	Functional Hightlights:
</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Overloads Ember's <code>TextInput</code> view with type set to <b>Number</b></li>
	<li>Adds CSS to remove unwanted visual toggle controls (this can be turned off)</li>
	<li>Adds Bootstraps 'form-control' class; disable with <code>bs="false"</code></li>
	<ul>
		<li>Sizing available as <code>size="large"</code>. Sizes are default, large, small.</li>
		<li>Allows color styling such <code>color="primary"</code>. Colors are default, primary, warning, info.</li>
		<li>Note: Bootstrap itself must be installed to leverage these features</li>
	</ul>
</ul>
	
<h3>Tests</h3>
<h4>Basics</h4>

<div class="container">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-xs-4">
			{{ui-number-input bs=false}}
		</div>
		<div class="col-xs-8">
			default use, nothing set<br/>
			<code>
\{{ui-number-input bs=false}}
